title: Fused Deposition Modeling (FDM)
description: FDM is one of the most common 3D printing technologies. It works by heating and extruding thermoplastic filament layer by layer to create the desired object. This method is widely used for rapid prototyping and desktop 3D printing.

title: Stereolithography (SLA)
description: SLA uses a UV laser to solidify liquid resin layer by layer to create the object. It offers high-resolution printing and is commonly used in applications where high detail and smooth surface finish are required.
